  "text": "## Access Log Format Field Completeness Audit\n\nThis audit identifies all C++ source files in envoyproxy/envoy that implement access log command operators for %REQ%, %RESP%, %DURATION%, and %UPSTREAM_HOST%.\n\n### Core Implementation Files\n\n#### 1. **%REQ% and %RESP% Operators** (HTTP Request/Response Headers)\n- **Implementation**: `source/common/formatter/http_specific_formatter.h` and `.cc`\n- **Classes**: \n  - `RequestHeaderFormatter` (line 98 in .h): Implements %REQ% operator for accessing request headers\n  - `ResponseHeaderFormatter` (line 115 in .h): Implements %RESP% operator for accessing response headers\n- **Registration**: `HttpBuiltInCommandParser::getKnownFormatters()` (line 331 in .cc) registers both operators\n- **Registration Mechanism**: `REGISTER_BUILT_IN_COMMAND_PARSER(HttpFormatterContext, HttpBuiltInCommandParser)` at end of .cc file\n\n#### 2. **%DURATION% Operator** (Request Duration)\n- **Implementation**: `source/common/formatter/stream_info_formatter.cc`\n- **Class**: `StreamInfoDurationFormatterProvider` (line 620 in .cc)\n- **Lookup Entry**: Line 1034 in `getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders()` function\n- **Calculation**: Extracts current duration from StreamInfo and converts to milliseconds\n\n#### 3. **%UPSTREAM_HOST% Operator** (Upstream Host Address)\n- **Implementation**: `source/common/formatter/stream_info_formatter.cc`\n- **Class**: `StreamInfoAddressFormatterProvider` (line 677 in .cc)\n- **Lookup Entry**: Line 1084 in `getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders()` function\n- **Method**: `withPort()` static method for extracting upstream host address with port\n\n### Core Formatter Architecture\n\n#### Parser and Registration\n1. **SubstitutionFormatParser** (`source/common/formatter/substitution_formatter.h`)\n   - Parses format strings containing `%COMMAND(SUBCOMMAND):LENGTH%` patterns\n   - Uses regex to identify and extract command components\n   - Delegates to registered command parsers for specific command handling\n\n2. **BuiltInCommandParsersBase** (`envoy/formatter/substitution_formatter_base.h`)\n   - Template base class for managing built-in command parser registration\n   - Provides `REGISTER_BUILT_IN_COMMAND_PARSER` macro for static registration\n   - Maintains list of available parsers for a given formatter context\n\n3. **Command Parser Lookup Tables**\n   - HTTP operators: `HttpBuiltInCommandParser::getKnownFormatters()` in `http_specific_formatter.cc` (line 331)\n   - StreamInfo operators: `getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders()` in `stream_info_formatter.cc` (line 821)\n\n#### Supporting Infrastructure\n1. **SubstitutionFormatUtils** (`source/common/formatter/substitution_format_utility.h/cc`)\n   - Provides `CommandSyntaxChecker` for validating operator syntax\n   - Utility functions for header parsing and protocol conversion\n\n2. **SubstitutionFormatStringUtils** (`source/common/formatter/substitution_format_string.h`)\n   - Proto-based configuration utilities\n   - Parses formatter configurations and integrates with factory system\n\n### Implementation Pattern\n\nAll operators follow a consistent pattern:\n1. Define a class inheriting from `FormatterProvider` (HTTP) or `StreamInfoFormatterProvider` (StreamInfo)\n2. Implement `formatWithContext()` and `formatValueWithContext()` methods\n3. Register the formatter via lookup table with command syntax flags and creation function\n4. Syntax flags specify: `COMMAND_ONLY`, `PARAMS_REQUIRED`, `PARAMS_OPTIONAL`, `LENGTH_ALLOWED`\n\n### Key Integration Points\n\n- **Line 87-94** in `substitution_formatter.h`: Built-in command parser invocation\n- **Line 334-420** in `http_specific_formatter.cc`: HTTP formatter lookup table\n- **Line 821-1200+** in `stream_info_formatter.cc`: StreamInfo formatter lookup table\n- Default format string defined at line 445-450 in `http_specific_formatter.cc` uses all four operators"
}

